Australian **personal loan rates** range from approximately 7.5–8.5% for secured loans to 10–16% for unsecured loans from banks and credit unions. Credit card debt at 18–22% can often be consolidated into a personal loan at a lower rate — saving thousands in interest.

This calculator shows monthly repayments, total interest, and the estimated comparison rate (which includes fees) for any personal loan. Enter your loan amount, rate, term, and establishment fee to see the true cost before you apply.
